parsed.explanation: The item number '20.' was wrapped in an <ID> tag. Descriptive text regarding the condition and binding of the first book was enclosed in a <NOTE> tag. The corrupted price marker '√†' was removed as redundant noise preceding the tagged price. The second bibliographic entry (<BIBL>Corpore Juris</BIBL>) was missing its closing tag, which was added. Finally, the entire exchange condition clause was wrapped in a second <NOTE> tag to clearly delineate the terms of trade.
